title: Several Dead After Mass Shooting in Hamburg, Germany
description: A police spokesman said there were no indications that a shooter remained at large.

title: Honduras Lifts Longtime Ban on ‘Morning After’ Pills
description: President Xiomara Castro signed an executive order on Wednesday, lifting a 2009 ban on emergency contraceptive pills.

title: Your Friday Briefing: Australia’s U.S. Nuclear Submarine Deal
description: Also, Russia hits targets across Ukraine.

title: Satellite images show widespread destruction after heavy fighting in Bakhmut
description: New satellite pictures of the eastern Ukrainian city, where a brutal battle has been raging for months, showed bridges over a strategically important river had been destroyed.

title: Georgia Protests Quiet Down as Government Pulls Back Russian-Style Law
description: But opposition leaders dismissed the move and warned that the government had not given up hope.

title: Russia’s Use of Hypersonic Missiles in Ukraine Raises Questions
description: Moscow fired more of the air-launched weapons ever used in a single wave since the war began a year ago

title: Nigeria Postpones State Elections Amid Presidential Vote Controversy
description: The government moved elections scheduled for Saturday back by a week, saying it needed more time to reset digital voting machines at the center of fraud accusations.

title: Questions surround Russia’s use of hypersonic missiles in its latest attack.
description: Moscow fired more of the air-launched weapons ever used in a single wave since the war began a year ago

title: Latvia Is Sending Cars Seized From Drunken Drivers to Ukraine
description: The first batch of cars will start making their way on Friday, the head of a charity helping deliver them said, and will go to the military and hospitals.

title: Cyclone Freddy Lashes Mozambique and Madagascar
description: The storm, which has killed 21 people already, has hit several countries in southeastern Africa and is on track to last longer than the record of 31 days.

title: These Morning-After Pills May Prevent STI’s, Researchers Say
description: Taking a common antibiotic after sex greatly reduces the chances of developing syphilis, chlamydia and gonorrhea among men who have sex with men and among trans women.

title: Australia to Buy U.S. Nuclear-Powered Submarines in Deal to Counter China
description: The arrangement also involves submarine construction by Britain and deepens a strategic partnership that the three countries have formed as China continues to build up its military.

title: Mass Protests Over Government’s Court Plans Sweep Israel
description: A demonstration against the government’s proposed judicial overhaul blocked a road to Israel’s main airport, disrupting a visit by the U.S. defense secretary.

title: Zaporizhzhia Nuclear Power Outage Amid Russian Shelling Prompts Fiery U.N. Response
description: It’s the sixth time the facility had to move to its emergency power supply since Russia invaded Ukraine a year ago.

title: Live Updates: Several Killed in Early Morning Attacks Across Ukraine
description: Russia launched its broadest barrage of missiles in nearly a month, striking residential areas and knocking out power in multiple areas. The attacks used some of Moscow’s most sophisticated weapons.

title: The Debate Over Covid’s Origin
description: Both U.S. political parties are now open to the idea that Covid may have come from a lab in China.

title: Colorful, Iconic Jeepneys May Soon Be Off the Road in the Philippines
description: The passenger vehicles have been ubiquitous for decades. The way the government wants to replace them with pricey new minibuses is rankling operators.

title: The Russian Singer Shaman Changes His Tune to Support Putin
description: As the Kremlin seeks to remake Russia’s institutions to comport with its militaristic worldview, cultural figures are picking a side. One singer made his choice — and is growing rich.

title: African Countries Made Huge Gains in Life Expectancy. Now That Could Be Erased.
description: Incidence of illnesses such as diabetes and hypertension are climbing quickly in most sub-Saharan countries, but the conditions are rarely diagnosed or treated.

title: Georgia’s Governing Party Plans to Withdraw Foreign Agents Bill After Protests
description: Opposition lawmakers had said the legislation mimicked a similar one in Russia that has been used to clamp down on dissent.

title: Your Thursday Briefing
description: Criticism in the U.S. of Israel’s judicial overhaul plan.

title: McCarthy Turns Down Zelensky’s Invitation to Visit Ukraine
description: In an interview with CNN, the Ukrainian leader had said the House speaker should go see firsthand what’s happening.

title: Mexicans Question Government’s Swift Response to Attack on Americans
description: Many noted the coordinated action after four Americans were kidnapped, and two killed, in a country where crimes against Mexicans get far less attention.

title: Russia Lacks Firepower to Keep Advancing, U.S. Intelligence Chief Says
description: While both Ukrainians and Russians say the pitched battle for the city of Bakhmut could determine whether Russia can pursue more of an offensive, Western officials are skeptical.

title: G.O.P. Inquiry on Afghan Withdrawal Opens With Searing Witness Accounts
description: The first House Foreign Affairs Committee hearing on the U.S. withdrawal from Afghanistan featured emotional and graphic testimony from two American service members who lived through it.
